    'A career in institutional philanthropy gave them a sharp eye for which projects sustain themselves and which collapse the moment the grant ends. They built a program dedicated to the unglamorous middle layer of the dweb — the maintainers, the standards, the documentation. Their freedom from profit pressure is real, but it''s replaced by a different master: the donor narrative, the annual report, the deliverable that proves the money did something legible.',
