    'Manages a fund pooled directly from a dweb community''s members. No exit logic, no donors — but limited capital and a hard mandate to serve members first.',
    'They emerged from a tenant-union-style organizing tradition and brought its financial discipline to the dweb: dues in, transparent allocation out, every member with a say. The treasury is small but uniquely legitimate — it answers to no outside power. That legitimacy is also its constraint: the steward cannot deploy a cent toward anything members haven''t agreed serves them, no matter how strategically promising it might be to the wider ecosystem.',
