    'A sharp, well-capitalized VC who genuinely believes the dweb will win — and intends to own a meaningful slice of the upside when it does. Pushes tokenization, growth, and clean exits.',
    'Unlike the reformed patient backer, this investor never had the crisis of faith. They see the platform-State''s decline as the largest value-creation event of the decade and the dweb as the vehicle. They are not a villain — their capital is real and can move projects from prototype to production overnight. But every term sheet bends a project toward capturable value, token markets, and an eventual liquidity event, which is precisely the logic that produced the platform-State in the first place.',
