    'Funds what has already proven it works, rewarding demonstrated impact rather than promises. Brilliant for sustaining winners, useless for unproven bets.',
    'A reaction against the waste of speculative grantmaking, this funder pioneered retroactive public-goods funding in the dweb: build first, prove the value, and the reward follows. It has reliably channeled large sums to maintainers and tools that the ecosystem actually came to depend on. Its blind spot is structural — nothing unproven, experimental, or early ever qualifies, so the most fragile and most important early-stage work goes unfunded until it''s already survived without help.',
