    'Designs the foundational interoperability layer that other dweb projects build on. Values elegant, durable standards and resists the fragmentation that fractures the ecosystem.',
    'A consensus researcher who chose to work on the boring, load-bearing parts of the stack — the addressing, the data formats, the bridges — because that''s where lock-in or freedom is actually decided. They carry the conviction that an ecosystem with five incompatible standards is just five small platform-States in waiting. This makes them a natural coordinator and an occasional obstacle: their insistence on getting the standard right can read as gatekeeping to builders who just want to ship.',
