    'Ships genuinely usable apps for low-connectivity and on-the-move users — the nomads the scenario centers. Pragmatic, fast, and willing to cut corners the architects hate.',
    'They learned their trade building for places where bandwidth is scarce, intermittent, or surveilled, and they have no patience for elegant protocols that assume a fat, free pipe. Their apps sync opportunistically, degrade gracefully, and meet users where they actually are. The trade-off is that shipping for real conditions sometimes means routing around the "correct" standard, which puts them in recurring friction with the protocol architect and anyone who prizes purity over a working product.',
