    'Keeps the relays, bridges, indexers, and storage alive — the invisible labor everyone depends on and almost no one funds. Chronically under-resourced and quietly indispensable.',
    'They run the unglamorous machinery that makes "decentralized" actually work: the relays that pass messages, the bridges between networks, the storage that doesn''t disappear. When it works, no one notices; when it breaks, the whole ecosystem feels it. They carry a long-term load that funders rarely reward and founders rarely thank, and they hold real, underappreciated leverage — because if they walk away, large parts of the network simply go dark.',
