    'They understand that "decentralized" software running on three cloud providers and two undersea cables isn''t decentralized at all. Their work is the literal substrate of nomad infrastructure: networks that move with people, run off-grid, and answer to no carrier or hyperscaler. It''s slow, physical, capital-hungry work that doesn''t scale like software, but it''s the only thing that makes true exit from the platform-State possible rather than rhetorical.',
