    'An elite engineer who left a dominant platform to build the dweb. Brings world-class skills — and the deep, unexamined habits of centralization that built the platform-State.',
    'They can architect systems at a scale almost no one else in the room can, and they came to the dweb sincerely, disillusioned with what they helped build. The danger is in their reflexes: the defaults they reach for — a central coordinator "just for now," a managed service "for reliability," a metrics pipeline "to understand users" — are exactly the patterns that quietly recentralize a decentralized system. Their contribution is enormous and their instincts are a standing risk the others must watch.',
